{"body": "Also, @mikekelly asked me to make something perfectly clear, so here it is:\r\n\r\nI think that standards should be followed, because they're standards. They're the working agreements that we all go by, and if we discover that we're not compliant, software should changed based on that and nothing else. This doesn't mean they're infallible, and when they get revised, things should be changed again. Because compliance with a spec is the most important thing.\r\n\r\nWe now return to your regularly scheduled pull request.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3204728", "created_at": "2011-12-19T15:45:53Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/505#issuecomment-3204728", "updated_at": "2011-12-19T15:45:53Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 505, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/steveklabnik", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/233c279c012ebac792aaa805f966cbc7?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F0c22d45f31acf0f4192c8c12b7a55dee.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/received_events", "gravatar_id": "233c279c012ebac792aaa805f966cbc7", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "steveklabnik", "type": "User", "id": 27786, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52385f14bd3543c15101215c"}, "id": 3204728, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/505